text: Musk had already acquired a large position in Twitter. The question is whether by tweeting out the question he was essentially acting as an activist - intending to influence the management of Twitter - not a passive but more of an activist's approach which perhaps would require

a 13D and not the 13G filing he made. Given the repeated conflicts between Musk and the SEC - might the SEC be returning to question Musk's actions on Twitter before today's disclosure? Quite possibly. @jimcramer @tomkeene @ferrotv @ScottWapnerCNBC @SquawkCNBC
